  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Actually, nothing made it necessary, but [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] one day, we had communication from somewhere-- and I don't recall how the news got to us anymore-- that my mother, who was a fairly heavy smoker, and in the bank vaults wasn't allowed to smoke, used the anonymity of the night to come down and to have a cigarette.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The rumor had it that there was no-- no catching of Jews to happen that night, that it was a peaceful night.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Somehow, you heard when danger was supposed to be.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were always people who had inside information.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My mother allegedly went out to have a cigarette, and walked up and down the building.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know how and who saw her, but this was indeed the giveaway, and the vaults were raided.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were told when-- my sister and I were told when we were first going to Gustav's home-- and his wife was Helen, and she deserves to be mentioned too-- that in case anything went wrong, my mother wanted to make sure that there is another auxiliary possibility for us to hide.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She had a friend from her school days-- from her secondary school days, or maybe university days, I'm not sure-- who was a doctor, and supposedly a good friend of my mother's and father's, a married man with children himself.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He was the only outsider who knew, other than the person who hid us, that we actually were still there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We were getting frantic with the situation of lying still and not being able to do anything.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At that point, I think I have to digress that I think I became unaware, really, what was real and what was imagined anymore.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
